widgets_values: It is best to set the max_people value to be bigger than or equal to the number of characters in the input image.
If you got a size error, try changing the divisible_by value to 32.
Enable this group, if you want better camera control. But this will slow down the process.
For quick movements, best to increase the frame rate to 24 or 30 or above, or else you may miss some moves. And generally, you get better result with higher frame rate.
a group of women is dancing

For the "index 1 is out of bounds for axis 0 with size 1" error. Please unlink the dw_poses from Pose Detection VitPose to DWPose node and ref_dw_pose from the Render NLF Poses node. This will fix the error. 
This may occur when you use a full-body input image and a half-body reference video. Or vise verse.

If you want an additional pose for better alignment. You could link it back.
